Business Brief -- Toys `R' Us Inc.:
   Net for Feb. 1 Period Rose
   10% on Sales Jump of 12%
Analysts said that sales were somewhat better than
expected but that gross profit margins in the quarter were
constrained both by price cutting and a shift in the total
product mix toward more traditional toys resulting from
slower sales of video game software.
   During the year the Paramus, N.J., company opened 46 toy
stores in the U.S. and 29 stores in Canada, France, Germany,
Taiwan and the United Kingdom.
   For the 52 weeks ended Feb. 1 net was $339.5 million, or
$1.15 a share, compared with net of $326 million, or $1.11 a
share, for the 53 weeks ended Feb. 2, 1991. Sales were $6.12
billion compared with $5.51 billion for the 53 weeks ended
Feb. 2, 1991.